<br>
While studying up on spells the other day for my newly leveled 39 enchanter, Amourador, I noticed the spell &quot;Gift of Magic.&quot;  Cooool, a spell that adds 50 mana to mana capacity!!!  But only available in Velious, at Iceclad or Thurgadin.  <br>
<br>
Being a semi-coward, I had never ventured to Thurgadin before, figuring that the newts had it locked down pretty tight.  But I was on lunch break, with about 1/2 hour to spend, and I figured I could run my 54 level druid Ammaron in to try to pick up the spell from the Cleric guild.  Buff up and off I go from PoK, through the stone to Great Divide, along the wall to the river, up the river into Thurgadin.<br>
<br>
With a air of &quot;little-boy&quot; excitement I zone into Thurgadin, not knowing what to expect.  Zone in, /who, and woot, the zone is empty except for me!!!  Ha ha, with visions of mana dancing in my head, I dash off for the center of the city.  I get almost to middle of city, and my keyboard stops responding.  I start right clicking and minor beating on my keyboard, and the big black screen with &quot;DISCONNECTED&quot; comes up.  What the heck!!!??  What happened??!  I wait for the computer to cycle through, try to get back on server, can't access.  Try to access another web site, I have no Internet connection.  (I am running out of time, lunch is over).  <br>
<br>
After a quick little investigation, I notice that just as I got to my critical point, the power adapter to the cable modem fell out of the wall socket and disconnected power to the cable modem.  Talk about Murphy's law!!!  What is the probability of that happening?  Well, lunch is over, I quickly plug the power adapter back in the socket, duct tape the power adapter to the wall, and since it sometimes takes our cable modem 1/2 hour to reset itself, I just head back to work, unsure what I will find when I finally reconnect.<br>
<br>
I just couldn't believe my odds of my cable modem self disconnecting at that exact moment.  The plug has maybe fallen out say once every 6 months?<br>
<br>
